  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large pot with a matching lid, with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pancetta lardons</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 4 min or until crispy and starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-pancetta-conchiglie/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken&nbsp;</strong><strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;in 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-pancetta-conchiglie/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>conchiglie</strong> and <strong>chicken stock</strong> to the <strong>pancetta</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>sugar</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-pancetta-conchiglie/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cover with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 7 min</p>\r\n<p>Tip:&nbsp;stir occasionally to ensure that the pasta has not stuck to the base of the pot</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-pancetta-conchiglie/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-pancetta-conchiglie/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 7 min, remove the lid from the pasta</p>\r\n<p>Stir continuously for 4-5 min or until a sauce has formed and the pasta is cooked, adding more water if it looks too dry</p>\r\n<p>Tip: stirring the sauce releases the starch from the pasta making it naturally creamier!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-pancetta-conchiglie/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta is cooked, remove the pot from the heat and stir in half of the <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>chives</strong> and the<strong> soft cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-and-pancetta-conchiglie/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pasta</strong> and garnish with the remaining <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>chives</strong> and a good grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
